<issue
   id="RBN-2"
   type="arm"
   linkend="Hybrid_breakdown_arm"
   status="closed"
   category="editorial"
   by="Rob Bodington"
   date="03-02-24">
<description>
  <p>
    A hybrid breakdown should enable the relationship between different breakdown
    element definitions of different types, e.g. physical_element_definition
    related to zone_element_definition. This model does not enable this.
  </p>
  <p>
    Hybrid_element_definition and Hybrid_breakdown_version are not required
    and should be deleted.
  </p>
  <p>
    Hybrid_element_usage should simply be a subtype of
    Breakdown_element_usage to allow the relationship of any subtype of breakdown_element_definition.
  </p>

</description>

<comment
   by="Rob Bodington"
   date="03-04-11">
<description>
  Raised as UK ballot comment.
</description>
</comment>
